SIMPLE: factious
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Factious
<hw>Fac"tious</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>factiosus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>factieux</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Given to faction; addicted to form parties and raise dissensions,
in opposition to government or the common good; turbulent; seditious;
prone to clamor against public measures or men; -- said of
persons.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Factious</qex> for the house of Lancaster.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Pertaining to faction; proceeding from faction;
indicating, or characterized by, faction; -- said of acts or
expressions; <as>as, <ex>factious</ex> quarrels</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Headlong zeal or <qex>factious</qex> fury.</q>
<rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Fac"tious*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Fac"tious*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Factitious</ent>⟦br⟧
